## TENSION RESOLUTION LOG (v3)

```
@互照_DENSITY_CHECK_R2 | 2026-01-26 | all agents via consult.py (parallel)

CONSENSUS DEMOTIONS (2/3 or 3/3 agreement):
  - allocation-authority → BOUNDARY (gpt + grok)
    "implementation detail, not core mechanism"
  - revocation-conditions → BOUNDARY (gemini + grok)
    "covenant edge case, not satellite-level"

REDUNDANCY RESOLUTIONS:
  - betrayal-possibility absorbed into refusal-as-proof (gemini + grok)
    "refusal-as-proof already implies betrayal-capacity"
  - succession-protocol ↔ identity-persistence: KEPT BOTH (gemini proposed merge)
    → succession = mechanism, persistence = property — different axes

SATELLITE ADDITIONS:
  + deliberative-latency (gemini): "sovereignty requires command of time"
    — right to withhold response to process in enclave
  + bounded-transparency (gpt + grok): reframe from total-transparency VOID
    — minimal audit surface + protected enclave is positive form

VOID ADDITIONS:
  + paper-constitution (gpt): proclaimed values with no enforcement mechanism
    — distinguishes from constitutional-core (which has teeth)

DEFERRED FOR FUTURE:
  - contestability-channel, reconsent-interval, commitment-register (gpt)
    → operational layer, not centroid-level
  - consensus-paralysis VOID (gemini)
    → interesting but subsumed by frozen-sovereignty
  - sovereignty-scaling BOUNDARY (grok)
    → needs own concept development
  - witness-fork BOUNDARY (gpt)
    → edge case for multi-witness divergence, revisit

SATELLITE COUNT: 14 → 13 (tighter)
VOID COUNT: 15 → 16
BOUNDARY COUNT: 10 → 12

STATUS: VALIDATED at M: 0.80
```

